==Knowledge==
{{See also|Sociology of scientific knowledge}}
''[[Sociology of knowledge]]'' is the study of the relationship between human thought and the social context within which it arises, and of the effects prevailing ideas have on societies.

*{{cite book|last=Mannheim|first=Karl |author-link=Karl Mannheim |others=Translated from the German ''Ideologie und Utopie'' by Louis Wirth and Edward Shils|title=Ideology and utopia : an introduction to the sociology of knowledge|year=1985|publisher=Harcourt Brace Jovanovich|location=San Diego|isbn=978-0-15-643955-8|edition=Facsimile |origyear=1936}}
*{{cite book|last=Berger|first=Peter L.|author-link=Peter L. Berger |last2=Luckmann |first2=Thomas |author2-link=Thomas Luckmann |title=[[The Social Construction of Reality|The social construction of reality : a treatise in the sociology of knowledge]]|year=1991|publisher=Penguin Books|location=London|isbn=978-0-14-013548-0 |edition=reprint |origyear=1966}}{{sfn|Edles|Appelrouth|2010|pp=276-277}}
*{{cite book|last=Bloor|first=David|title=Knowledge and social imagery|year=1991|publisher=University of Chicago Press|location=Chicago|isbn=978-0-226-06097-2|edition=2nd |origyear=1976}}
:Gave rise to the field known as Science and Technology Studies.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Critical notice: David Bloor's ''Knowledge and Social Imagery''|edition=Second |journal=Philosophy of Science |volume=60 |year=1993 |pages=158&ndash;170 |issue=1| doi = 10.1086/289724 |last1=Fuller |first1=Steve }}</ref>

*{{cite book |first=Bruno |last=Latour|author-link=Bruno Latour |first2=Steve |last2=Woolgar |title=[[Laboratory Life|Laboratory Life: The Social Construction of Scientific Facts]]|year=1979|publisher=Sage Publications|location=Beverly Hills, Calif|isbn=0-8039-0993-4}}
:Ethnography of microbiologists working at the Salk Institute.  Explains the elevation of observations to the level of fact through a system of credibility. Started the ethnographic laboratory studies movement in the sociology of knowledge.

*{{cite book |last=Fleck|first=Ludwik |author-link=Ludwik Fleck |editor-first=Thaddeus J. |editor-last=Trenn |editor2-first=Robert K. |editor2-last=Merton |editor2-link=Robert K. Merton|translator=Fred Bradley|translator2=Thaddeus J. Trenn |others=Foreword by Thomas S.|title=Genesis and development of a scientific fact|year=1981|publisher=University of Chicago Press|location=Chicago|isbn=978-0-226-25325-1|edition=Phoenix}}

==Politics==
''[[Political sociology]]'' was traditionally concerned with how social trends, dynamics, and structures of domination affect formal political processes, as well as exploring how various social forces work together to change political policies.<ref>Nachtigal M. Paul."Political Trends Affecting Nonmetropolitan America." Journal of Research in Rural Education Vol.10(1994):161-166.Print. From:http://www.jrre.psu.edu/articles/v10,n3,p161-166,Nachtigal.pdf</ref> Now it is also concerned with the formation of identity through social interaction, the politics of knowledge and other aspects of social relations.
*{{cite book|last=Mills|first=C. Wright |author-link=C. Wright Mills|others=With a new afterword by Alan Wolfe|title=[[The Power Elite]]|year=2000|origyear=1958|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-513354-7|edition=New}}<ref name=EdlesMills/>
*{{cite book|title=Who Rules America? |first= G. William |last=Domhoff |author-link=G. William Domhoff |publisher=Prentice-Hall |location=Englewood Cliffs, NJ |year=1967}}
**{{cite book|last=Domhoff|first=G. William|author-mask=1 |title=Who rules America? : power and politics, and social change|year=2006|publisher=McGraw-Hill|location=Boston, Mass|isbn=978-0-07-287625-3|edition=5th}}
*{{cite book|title=[[States and Social Revolutions|States and Social Revolutions: a comparative analysis of France, Russia, and China]] |first=Theda |last=Skocpol |author-link=Theda Skocpol|publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=1979 |isbn= 978-0-521-29499-7}}
*{{cite book|first=Frances Fox |last=Piven |author-link=Frances Fox Piven |first2=Richard |last2=Cloward |author2-link=Richard Cloward |publisher=Pantheon Books|year=1988|title=Why Americans Don't Vote}}
